This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of shared registers, which are a fundamental concept in concurrent data structures, indicating that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also proposes an efficient construction method, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of timestamp systems to solve concurrency control problems suggests that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on distributed algorithms and vector clocks further supports its classification under the Distributed (cs.Distributed) sub-category.
